p.hi:
; an
                        orbital ring with a temporal bar more or less complete; columella present;
                        parietal bone single.

div.p:
Europo-Asiatic genera: Bunopus, Ceramodactylus, Teratoscincus,
                        Agamura. These inhabit only the southern parts of the region in Asia;
                    representatives of some African or Indian genera (viz., Ptyodactylus, Tarentola, Gymnodactylus, and Stenodactylus) likewise extend into this region.
